The paper deals with a low complexity receiver structure for MIMO communication systems, which involves interference removal and estimation of transmitted symbols. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of factor graphs and graph-based algorithms, which are commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of M-QAM modulation is also mentioned, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
